data.output: One evening, after a long trip to see family I was about to make my way to take the long drive home, around 2 hours away. I had had a fun time, but honestly I was just exhausted. I opened the door and went to turn the keys, ready to leave, I would miss my family but it was time to make my own departure. I turned the keys, but rather than the usual hum I would expect to hear I just hear a harsh sound resonating from the engine. Something is wrong, this is not normal. I make my way out of the car and back to the house I had just moments ago been so delighted to depart from.  "Hey everyone, i'm back." I announced, with a twinge of disappointment in my voice. "It seems my car isn't starting, did anything happen to it while I was here?" "Well, actually" my youngest sibling spoke up. She had recently got a license of her own, so it was surprising she would be the one to speak up about issues with a car. "We don't have a station nearby, so I had hoped to help out a bit by pumping some of our own fuel in before you left!" There was a look of confusion across the family, no one sure what she meant by our own fuel. "Wait, you didn't specify. What kind of fuel was it?" I replied to her. "Oh! It was a canister of diesel, every car uses that nowadays, right?" she gleefully explained. There was a heavy silence across the room, especially on the adults. I took a breath before uttering "My car only uses petrol...".
